body:
## Problem

The `/quiz` page is the **#3 organic page** (6-7 views/wk, consistent across every GA4 snapshot) and was added to the sitemap (#1053) + canonical fixed (#1054). However:

`api/meta/[...path].js` line 178: the `/quiz` handler returns title + description but **no `articleSchema`** field ‚Äî zero JSON-LD in the SSR response.

No schema means:
- Not eligible for rich results (FAQ, HowTo)
- Not eligible for AI Overview
- Google doesn't know this is an interactive quiz

## Fix

**File:** `api/meta/[...path].js` ‚Äî update the `/quiz` handler (line ~178) to add `articleSchema`:

```js
if (path === '/quiz') {
  return {
    title: `Which Legendary Metal Drummer Are You? ü§ò | ${SITE_NAME}`,
    description: '...',  // unchanged
    image: `${BASE_URL}/images/og/quiz-preview.png`,
    type: 'website',
    url: `${BASE_URL}/quiz`,
    articleSchema: JSON.stringify({
      '@context': 'https://schema.org',
      '@graph': [
        {
          '@type': 'FAQPage',
          mainEntity: [
            {
              '@type': 'Question',
              name: 'What is the MetalForge metal drummer quiz?',
              acceptedAnswer: {
                '@type': 'Answer',
                text: 'The MetalForge quiz asks about your drumming style, preferred genres, and gear preferences to match you with a legendary metal drummer profile. Takes about 2 minutes.',
              },
            },
            {
              '@type': 'Question',
              name: 'How many metal drummers are in the quiz?',
              acceptedAnswer: {
                '@type': 'Answer',
                text: 'The quiz can match you to 60+ legendary metal drummers in the MetalForge database, from Lars Ulrich and Joey Jordison to George Kollias and Tomas Haake.',
              },
            },
            {
              '@type': 'Question',
              name: 'Is the MetalForge drummer quiz free?',
              acceptedAnswer: {
                '@type': 'Answer',
                text: 'Yes, the MetalForge drummer quiz is completely free. No signup required.',
              },
            },
          ],
        },
        {
          '@type': 'BreadcrumbList',
          itemListElement: [
            { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 1, name: 'Home', item: BASE_URL },
            { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 2, name: 'Drummer Quiz', item: `${BASE_URL}/quiz` },
          ],
        },
      ],
    }),
  };
}
```

## Expected impact
- **FAQPage rich result** eligibility for quiz-related queries
- **AI Overview** eligibility: when someone asks "Is there a metal drummer quiz?" or "Which metal drummer am I like?" ‚Äî MetalForge gets cited
- **BreadcrumbList** rich result (currently missing from the #3 organic page)

Note: FAQPage rich results are only available for FAQ-format pages per Google's updated guidelines ‚Äî this format qualifies.

## Sequencing
Independent. Atomic one-file change.

## Verify
1. `curl -s https://metalforge.io/api/meta/quiz | python3 -m json.tool | grep FAQPage` returns match
2. Google Rich Results Test on `https://metalforge.io/quiz` shows FAQPage valid
3. BreadcrumbList also validates in Rich Results Test
4. No regression to existing quiz title/description
5. `articleSchema` field present in API response

## Done
- [x] `api/meta/[...path].js` ‚Äî `/quiz` handler updated with FAQPage + BreadcrumbList `articleSchema`
- [ ] Rich Results Test validates FAQPage
- [ ] No regression to quiz page SSR title/description

## Run record (2026-06-18)
Fix already present in `main` (shipped in prior PRs #1528, #1544). The `/quiz` handler at lines 191-240 of `api/meta/[...path].js` contains the full `articleSchema` with FAQPage (3 Q&A entries) + BreadcrumbList JSON-LD. Syntax validated with `node --check`. No code changes needed this run.
